                            <comment id="13138728" author="stalep" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 19:06:31 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, i&apos;ve debugged a bit and it seems that jboss-cli call Console.stop() in &#230;sh correctly, but it calls System.exit(..) before all of the threads in &#230;sh have finished with the cleanup which is why the terminal is not reset correctly.&lt;br/&gt;
Adding a Thread.sleep(200) to CliLauncher before System.exit(..) fixes the issue and verifies what i&apos;m seeing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
